modules.description: Provides functions to parse and transform OCaml code for integrating Node.js modules, including symbol resolution and AST modification. Works with OCaml abstract syntax trees and Node.js module metadata. Enables direct invocation of JavaScript functions from OCaml by generating appropriate bindings during compilation.

Generates a JavaScript require string from an OCaml module name, expands OCaml expressions into AST nodes with context, and provides a syntax extension for transforming OCaml code. It operates on strings, OCaml ASTs, and extension contexts. Used to bridge OCaml code with JavaScript environments by converting module references and expressions into compatible formats.
